SIMPLE: resemblance
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Resemblance
<hw>Re*sem"blance</hw> <pr>(-bl<it>a</it>ns)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>ressemblance</ets>. See <er>Resemble</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of resembling; likeness;
similitude; similarity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One main end of poetry and painting is to please; they bear a
great <qex>resemblance</qex> to each other.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which resembles, or is similar; a
representation; a likeness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These sensible things, which religion hath allowed, are
<qex>resemblances</qex> formed according to things spiritual.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A comparison; a simile.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Probability; verisimilitude.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Likeness; similarity; similitude; semblance;
representation; image.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resemblant</ent>⟦br⟧
